<TITLE> Jodie Foster says gadgets drive her mad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TOKYO, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Two-time Oscar winner Jodie Foster plays a vengeance killer in her latest film, but in real life, she gets angry at electronic gadgets, not at people. "I have a problem with electronics. I can't ever make them work. It drives me crazy," she told a news conference in Tokyo on Tuesday to promote "The Brave One." In the thriller, Foster plays a Manhattan radio personality who goes on a killing spree after her fiancee is murdered in a Central Park attack. A reporter asked if there was anyone in real life she wanted to take revenge on. "It's the only time where I lose my temper, is on inanimate metal objects," she said, to chuckles from the audie
